# Enterprise Architecture for AI Systems

# Introduction

Enterprise AI Architecture focuses on designing:
- Scalable
- Secure
- Distributed
- Cloud-native
- Production-grade AI systems

for organizations operating large-scale Generative AI and LLM workloads.

Modern enterprise AI systems must support:
- Millions of users
- Multi-agent workflows
- RAG systems
- GPU orchestration
- Compliance
- High availability
- Multi-cloud deployments

---

# Why Enterprise AI Architecture Matters

Enterprise AI systems are:
- Complex
- Distributed
- Expensive
- Security-sensitive

Poor architecture can lead to:
- High latency
- Security risks
- Scaling failures
- Massive infrastructure costs

---

# Goals of Enterprise AI Architecture

| Goal | Description |
|---|---|
| Scalability | Handle massive workloads |
| Reliability | High uptime |
| Security | Enterprise-grade protection |
| Observability | Full system visibility |
| Cost efficiency | Optimized infrastructure |
| Governance | Compliance & auditing |

